This paper is about training a neural network language model, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of noise contrastive estimation (NCE) for training the model, which is a technique commonly used in machine learning (ML) for estimating parameters of a model. This suggests that the paper could also be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper presents experimental results on a specific dataset, which could make it relevant to the sub-category cs.SD (Sound).
